ergy management system."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Since scanners running on a live video feed can put a lot of load onto the CPU and\/or GPU"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"of the device, causing the battery to drain quickly and running the device hot, you can customize the energy"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"consumption using this class by configuring the rate of detections\/recognitions per second in performance mode as"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"well as in energy saving mode."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"In performance mode the scanners will be fed with a higher, configurable rate of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"video frames per second."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"After a certain, configurable period of inactivity the energy save mode will be engaged and the rate"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"of scans will be reduced to a lower (configurable) rate."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"You can also configure the time of inactivity before the automatic mode switches from performance to energy save mode."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Inactivity here means that both of the following conditions are met:"}],"role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"SBSDKBaseScannerEnergyConfiguration","kind":"identifier"}],"fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"SBSDKBaseScannerEnergyConfiguration","kind":"identifier"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/net.doo.ScanbotSDK\/documentation\/ScanbotSDK\/SBSDKBaseScannerEnergyConfiguration","type":"topic","title":"SBSDKBaseScannerEnergyConfiguration"}},"variantOverrides":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"occ"}],"patch":[{"value":"occ","path":"\/identifier\/interfaceLanguage","op":"replace"},{"value":"Type Property","path":"\/metadata\/roleHeading","op":"replace"},{"value":"defaultConfigurat